This paper is primarily focused on hyperparameter optimization in machine learning, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the need for distributed computing and productionization of machine learning workloads, which could fall under "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DC) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI), respectively. The paper also presents empirical results and design decisions related to the implementation of the hyperparameter optimization algorithm, which could fall under "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) and "Software Engineering" (cs.SE).
